{
  "stem": "1765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's not-- you get-- you know, people ask me, children ask me, how could you live like that?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one little girl wrote me a letter after a, a, a class visit I had in Great Neck.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she said, 'I learned that courage is not just doing a heroic deed, but to act without thinking while doing a frightening task,' a sixth grader.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, courage is, is not a heroic thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You just do what you have to do without thinking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Don't have potatoes, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you go to bed hungry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's not the end of the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You still get up in the morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not like you're starving to death.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we just never had enough food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, bread was the, the staple of the three meals a day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Occasionally, we had a piece of meat, if we sold something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I started doing things to earn some money or some food.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it was bartering.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one day, I was on, on the baracholka.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And before that, I knitted a sweater for a woman who was born with one arm.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she had a little girl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she knew I could knit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was taught knitting and embroidery and everything in Vilna, both in my school and by my mother and by Miss Rachel, my governess.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I knitted a sweater for this woman with one arm for her daughter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she paid me with food-- potatoes and bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So that gave me courage.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then one day, I met a woman named Maria Nikolaivna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her husband was a big shot in the village.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we talked in the baracholka.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she said, would I be willing to knit a sweater for her?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wrote about that.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
